{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"text":" that one should be aware of.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Store internals rewrite"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test your application after upgrading."}]},{"anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"StateObject compatibility"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftUI’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One important difference between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" is that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"eager, while "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s is lazy. Because of this, if you initialize a root "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"type":"text","text":" to be held"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":", stores will be initialized (and immediately discarded) whenever the parent view’s body"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is computed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To avoid the creation of these stores, one can now assign the store to a "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", instead:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct FeatureView: View {","  @StateObject var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  init() {","    _store = StateObject(","      \/\/ This expression is only evaluated the first time the parent view is computed.","      wrappedValue: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","        Feature()","      }","    )","  }","","  var body: some View { \/* ... *\/ }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ObservableObject"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance does not have any impact on the actual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"observability of the store. You should continue to rely on the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ObservableState()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" macro for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"observation."}]}],"style":"important","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Migratin